item.title: Taylor Swift joins Whitney Houston as the only female soloists to simultaneously chart three albums in the top 10 on the Billboard 200.
item.author: popcrave

item.title: ‘D-DAY’ by Agust D debuts at #2 on the Billboard 200 with 140,000 units (122,000 pure sales).
item.author: popcrave

item.title:
Taylor Swift charts three albums in the top 10 on the Billboard 200 this week:
#3: folklore: the long pond studio sessions #6: Midnights #10: Lover
item.author: popcrave

item.title:
‘folklore: the long pond studio sessions’ by @TaylorSwift13 debuts at #3 on the Billboard 200 with 75,000 units (all pure sales).
It becomes her 14th top 10 album on the chart.
item.author: popcrave

item.title: ‘One Thing At A Time’ by Morgan Wallen spends an 8th week at #1 on the Billboard 200, with 149,000 units.
item.author: popcrave
